# Fish Shell Environment

The user environment uses **Fish Shell**, not bash/zsh. Generate commands using Fish shell syntax only.

## ❗Important Syntax Differences:

| Purpose                        | Bash/Zsh Syntax         | Fish Shell Syntax        |
|-------------------------------|--------------------------|---------------------------|
| Redirect stdout               | `> file.txt`             | `> file.txt`              |
| Append stdout                 | `>> file.txt`            | `>> file.txt`             |
| Redirect stderr               | `2> file.txt`            | `^ file.txt`              |
| Append stderr                 | `2>> file.txt`           | `^>> file.txt`            |
| Redirect both stdout & stderr| `> file 2>&1` or `&>`     | `&> file.txt`             |
| Append both stdout & stderr  | `>> file 2>&1` or `&>>`   | `&>> file.txt`            |
| stderr → stdout for piping   | `2>&1 | ...`              | `^&1 | ...`               |

## Key Points:
- In fish, `^` represents stderr
- `&>` redirects both stdout and stderr
- Always use Fish-compatible syntax for terminal commands
- If unsure about syntax, ask for confirmation before proceeding

